itemDescription: Whitelaw, Annie Watt (1875–1966), headmistress and educationist

wikipedia_page.main: Annie Watt Whitelaw (17 August 1875 – 11 August 1966) was a British headmistress and educationist. She was a headteacher in New Zealand and the first NZ woman to attend Girton College and to lead a British school. She led religious orders and was the adviser on girls education in the British colonies.
